<p><span class="envidentifier">Definition 1.2.40
<span style="font-weight:normal;">([<a class='ref' data-tag="MR1940513">93</a>, p. 82])</span></span>
Let $\kappa$ be a cardinal. An inverse semigroup $S$ is <em>$\kappa$-distributive</em> if for every compatible set $F\subseteq S$ with $|F|<\kappa$, the supremum $\bigvee F$ exists and for all $z\in S$,
<div class="equation"\[
z\left(\bigvee F\right)=\bigvee(zF).
\]</div>
Note that $|zF|\leq |F|$ and $zF$ is compatible by Proposition <a class='ref' data-tag="refpropositioncompatibility" href="#propositioncompatibility">1.2.30</a>, and that $\left(\bigvee F\right)z=\bigvee(Fz)$ also holds by Proposition <a class='ref' data-target="refpropositionpropertiesofjoins" href="#propositionpropertiesofjoins">1.2.37</a>(b).
</p>
